      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "Grafana sees only **warp-mimir** and **warp-loki**, so pg-backed and ssh-backed signals cannot be charted here \u2014 they run in the monitor (`server/monitor`, SIGNALS.md is the catalog):\n\n- **1.1 pg contract rate / 1.2 canary + task health (\u00a77, \u00a712) / 1.3 active vs idle-in-tx state split / 2.x tier-1 pg (open-set, vacuum, stats landmine, task durations) / 2.8 selection freshness** \u2014 pg via ssh; no pg datasource is provisioned.\n- **\u00a73 per-node redis internals** \u2014 `urnetwork / redis cluster` charts the redis_* exporter series; the slowlog/latency/keyspace batteries (5.2\u20135.4, 3.3 family histogram, 9.1 config checks) are monitor-side redis-cli.\n- **\u00a75 escalation batteries, \u00a78 container-level deploy state** \u2014 ssh/docker on the edges.\n\nRelated boards: `urnetwork / redis cluster` (\u00a73), `urnetwork / host metrics`, `urnetwork / services overview` (process vitals + versions), `urnetwork / service logs` (drill-in)."
      }
